article.headline: Morehead St. 71, Samford 58
article.story: MOREHEAD, Ky. (AP) -- Quentin Pryor and Brandon Callahan each scored 15 points as Morehead State broke a nine-game losing streak with a 71-58 win Thursday night over Samford. Samford led 20-11 in the first half before being held scoreless for a little more than 7 minutes to end the half. An 11-2 run by Morehead State over the last eight minutes of the first half gave the Eagles a 25-22 advantage at the break. In the second half, Morehead State never lost the lead. A 3-pointer by Joe Ross Merritt brought the Bulldogs (14-13, 11-7 Ohio Valley Conference) to within 42-40 with 9:34 left. The largest lead, 64-47, for Morehead State came at 1:25 left. Jamyron Steward finished with a career high 14 points for Morehead State (11-15, 7-11). Randall Gulina paced Samford with 17 while Jerry Smith had 15 and Travis Peterson added 13. Morehead State hit 26-of-47 from the field (55.3 percent) while Samford was 17-of-49 (34.7 percent). The Eagles hit 6-of-14 3-point attempts while the Bulldogs finished 10-of-33. Morehead State also outrebounded Samford 34-25.
